This place is transcendentally good. I go here a lot because I feel like I don't go enough. This is a hidden halal gem that more people should know about.  Food: there are so many menu items here that are consistently excellent. The chicken, beef, and lamb shashlik (basically shish kabobs etc) are essentials. The Jibek Jolu Special, Jerovnya, Frikase and Lagman are also must-eats. Get the honey cake for dessert. Prices here are very reasonable despite the high quality of the food.  Service: the staff is nice, warm and responsive.  Atmosphere: the restaurant is comfortable enough and very clean. Parking in the back feels a little questionable but overall very manageable. The prayer space in the basement is a nice touch.
